Legend / Notes
Ambiguity Detection: identifies potential sources of hallucination caused by vague input.

Clarification Request: halts response until ambiguity is resolved; user actively participates.

User Clarifies: ensures the model only proceeds when intent is explicit.

Precise Response: prevents the model from filling gaps; aligns output with confirmed user intent.

Effect: CAP intercepts hallucinations at the root by addressing unclear input, rather than trying to smooth over uncertainty.
